AUSTRALIAN OPEN
February 8, 2021
Alexander Zverev
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
  A. ZVEREV/M. Giron
 6-7, 7-6, 6-3, 6-2
 THE MODERATOR:   Questions, please.
 Q. Sascha, tricky couple of opening sets today.  Could you tell me how the match went and how pleased you are to advance?
 ALEXANDER ZVEREV:   Yeah, first of all, I think it's incredible to play in front of fans again.  That's something that we missed over the last year or so.  I think that's great news for us, to be able to do that here.
 And yeah, it wasn't easy.  I still felt my abs and my back a little bit, so the serve wasn't full power like it usually is.  I barely got over 210 on the serve, which is still quite fast, but for me I know I can go faster than that, so I had to vary it a little bit.  I had to go a lot of spin, I had to go a lot of slice on that serve.  That was a little bit different.
 All in all, he played well, as well, and for me the longer the match went, the better I started playing, and that's something positive, I think.
   
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT